JOHANNESBURG - The ANC’s national working committee took a decisive step on Wednesday calling for North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo to resign voluntarily or be recalled, eNCA can confirm. Failure to heed the call would result in the committee's recommendation being taken to an emergency meeting of the ANC national executive committee for endorsement. The North West has been plagued with crises. WATCH: I welcome any probe against me: Supra Mahumapelo The provincial health department has been placed under administration after health workers went on strike and several hospitals and clinics were forced to close their doors. Violent protests against Mahumapelo have been staged in the provincial capital, Mahikeng, with demonstrators accusing his administration of corruption. eNCA